description: This project document will encompass the works prior to Stage I, and will only include excavation, land clearing, and leveling of the future Jericho Agro Industrial park. Approximately 18,000 workdays will be generated by the project.

subproject.corporate outcome: Expansion and access to financial services for the poor, employment and income generation and access to markets, goods and services.
subproject.description: As part of the Governemnt of Japan, "Corrdidor for peace and Prosperity" initiative, a feasability study was undertaken by the Japanese International Cooperation Agency (JICA) for the Development of a Agro-Industrial Park in the Jordan River Rift Valley. The study developed a three stage concept for the future works.
subproject.title: P1 - Construction of the Jeric
